          <msContents>
            <textLang mainLang="syr"/>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="true">
              <locus to="5" from="1"/>
              <title xml:lang="en">Hymns and Prayers</title>
              <note>Leaves from a manuscript, written in a small, neat hand of the ixth or xth cent.
                It seems to have contained hymns and prayers, the beginnings of some of which are
                still legible on foll. 3 b (ܐܚܪܢܐ in two places, at the top of the page), 4 a, b,
                and 5 a.</note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a2" n="2" defective="true">
              <locus to="11" from="6"/>
              <title xml:lang="en">Fragments from "the Obsequies of my Lady Mary"</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܠܘܘܝܗ̇ ܕܡܪܬܝ ܡܪܝܡ</rubric>
              <note>Six leaves from a manu¬script, written in two columns, in a fine Estrangela of
                the vth or vith cent. From what is legible on fol. 9 a, it appears that they
                belonged to the apocryphal work entitled "the Obsequies of my Lady Mary, "ܠܘܘܝܗ̇
                ܕܡܪܬܝ ܡܪܝܡ, <bibl>Add. 14,484, foll. 1— 8</bibl>. See above, <bibl>p. 99, no.
                  clviii.</bibl>
              </note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a3" n="3" defective="true">
              <locus to="24" from="12"/>
              <title xml:lang="en">Fragments of a Lectionary from the Gospels</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܟܬܒܐ ܕܦܘܪܫ ܩܪ̈ܝܢܐ</rubric>
              <note>Foll. 12—24. Thirteen leaves from a manuscript, written in a large Estrangela of
                about the xth cent., containing fragments of a Lectionary from the Gospels. On fol.
                12 b we can still discern the traces of the running title ܟܬܒܐ ܕܦܘܪܫ ܩܪ̈ܝܢܐ. To the
                same volume belonged Add. 14,451, fol. 88, and 14,452, fol. 58. </note>
              <note>These leaves, the upper and lower halves of which are not always correctly
                joined together, have been folded so as to form the following MS Item</note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem xml:id="a4" n="4" defective="true">
              <locus to="24" from="12"/>
              <title xml:lang="en">Fragments from an item containing a collection of hymns
                for the Vigils</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܩ̈ܠܐ ܫܗ̈ܪܢܝܐ ܐܘܟܝܬ ܓܘ̈ܫܡܐ</rubric>
              
              <note>A manuscript, about 5 1/2 in. by 4 1/4, written in an inelegant hand of the
                xiith cent. The quires are signed with letters, and the leaves have been numbered at
                a later period with Coptic arithmetical figures. It contains a collection of hymns
                for the Vigils ܩ̈ܠܐ ܫܗ̈ܪܢܝܐ ܐܘܟܝܬ ܓܘ̈ܫܡܐ, etc., ar¬ranged according to the eight
                tones.</note>
            </msItem>
